A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Titles 12, 25, and 33 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 conservation and natural resources, fire protection and safety, and insurance, respectively,
3 so as to provide greater health protections for firefighters; to provide for monitoring of
4 concentration levels of perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances, or PFAS, at certain
5 firefighter related sites; to prohibit the use of firefighting equipment containing PFAS as an
6 intentionally added chemical after a certain date; to require manufacturers of firefighting
7 equipment to label such equipment as containing PFAS as an intentionally added chemical
8 after a certain date; to provide for the development of standards for mitigating PFAS
9 contamination at harmful exposure levels and for the safe disposal or destruction of any
10 firefighting equipment containing PFAS as an intentionally added chemical; to create the
11 Firefighter Health Advisory Council and establish its powers; to provide for the
12 establishment and purpose of the Firefighter PFAS Initiative; to require fire departments to
13 provide and maintain insurance coverage for its firefighters for the payment of claims for
14 PFAS blood testing under certain circumstances; to require insurers to provide coverage for
15 PFAS blood testing under certain circumstances; to revise and provide definitions; to provide
16 for civil penalties; to provide for reporting; to provide for a short title; to provide for
17 legislative findings and intent; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
18 for other purposes.
