20 SECTION 1.
21 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Firefighter Health and Environmental
22 Safety Act."
23 SECTION 2.
24 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
25 (1) Firefighters face significant health risks due to occupational exposure to toxic
26 substances, including perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances, or PFAS; and
27 (2) Current federal and state health programs lack adequate provisions for addressing
28 occupational hazards unique to firefighting.
29 (b) It is the intent of the General Assembly to:
30 (1) Enhance firefighter health protections; and
31 (2) Ensure accountability and compliance with laws, rules, and regulations providing
32 health protections for firefighters through clear enforcement mechanisms.
