447 by subsection (c) of this Code section or more favorable to the insured than those required
448 by subsection (c) of this Code section.
449 (f) The provisions of this Code section shall apply to group accident and sickness
450 insurance policies issued by a fraternal benefit society, a healthcare plan, a health
451 maintenance organization, or any similar entity.
452 (g) Nothing contained in this Code section shall be deemed to prohibit the payment of
453 different levels of benefits or from having differences in coinsurance percentages
454 applicable to benefit levels for services provided by preferred and nonpreferred providers
455 as otherwise authorized under the provisions of Article 2 of this chapter, relating to
456 preferred provider arrangements."
457 SECTION 11.
458 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
